"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"Verification Protocol Every\",\n        \"kind\": \"proper_noun\",\n        \"path\": \"checklist.md\",\n        \"source\": \"derived\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"Code Quality\",\n        \"kind\": \"proper_noun\",\n        \"path\": \"checklist.md\",\n        \"source\": \"derived\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"causal_summary\": \"Conform the ~104 hyphenated + ~160 total mechanically-sliced reference/asset .md files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the canonical create-skill asset/reference templates: 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, snake_case filenames, H1 + intro + `## 1. OVERVIEW` before content, optional RELATED RESOURCES last. Every rename updates all in-hub references. Extends 027's underscore convention to the reference/asset split files 027 did not cover.\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-07-12T14:23:01.630Z\",\n    \"last_save_at\": \"2026-07-13T05:08:19.235Z\",\n    \"save_lineage\": \"graph_only\",\n    \"last_accessed_at\": null,\n    \"source_docs\": [\n      \"spec.md\",\n      \"plan.md\",\n      \"tasks.md\",\n      \"checklist.md\",\n      \"implementation-summary.md\"\n    ],\n    \"source_fingerprint\": \"sha256:15542ef6f30a69bea99a5e0dbd93354c5e2c28ecd1864096a5221db031bca6c8\",\n    \"source_doc_hashes\": {\n      \"spec.md\": \"dd345226556a8bb9abc4de80b9d59ae293004196cf024385b72c3070cd39a617\",\n      \"plan.md\": \"aad345aa84428ebb8d4bbcbe8b85caeb8719eba60117b6363c998c89036fa947\",\n      \"tasks.md\": \"ed18a119344bf9701a36033a2f49bcaf03bbe7b890e3d1d0c9145649c0daeb02\",\n      \"checklist.md\": \"63ce2b53de438995644f0211fdeadd119e93fb41d8e3b966e34f2a64871bb5fb\",\n      \"implementation-summary.md\": \"7455fb71bcd716984cbfaf82915ee354fd69043a092de004730ea575fe8d599c\"\n    },\n    \"last_active_child_id\": null,\n    \"last_active_at\": null\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":215,"totalLines":215,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1783921274012,"end":1783921274063}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04843a2490066c82016a547a79cb348191943515b2006e4f13"}},"id":"prt_f59fe6c9b001qBv5BOeOa9Xy7I","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f59fe12ab001kpdOndufCVF3tM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921274073,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_G4wlyZ2A2Ij39vRmO7xGSZ58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Review Core Doctrine\n3: description: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"findings first severity ordering\"\n6:   - \"review finding schema\"\n7:   - \"severity contract for merge decisions\"\n8:   - \"evidence file line citation\"\n9:   - \"baseline surface precedence\"\n10:   - \"baseline check families\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.5.0.11\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Review Core Doctrine\n17: \n18: Shared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## 2. SEVERITY DEFINITIONS\n29: \n30: | Level | Meaning | Handling |\n31: | --- | --- | --- |\n32: | P0 | Blocker: exploitable security issue, auth bypass, destructive data loss | Block merge |\n33: | P1 | Required: correctness bug, spec mismatch, must-fix gate issue | Fix before merge |\n34: | P2 | Suggestion: non-blocking improvement, documentation polish, style or maintainability follow-up | Optional or schedule follow-up |\n35: \n36: Escalation rule: if confidence is low but impact is high, classify toward the higher severity and state the uncertainty explicitly.\n37: \n38: ### Numeric Severity Calibration\n39: \n40: Numeric scores are advisory context, not the gate. A reviewer may add an optional `riskScore` to a finding and adjust it by `+/-2` for local context such as exploitability, blast radius, user impact, confidence, or proven containment. The merge/block decision remains the severity contract above: `P0` blocks, `P1` requires remediation, and `P2` is advisory. Do not adopt `score>=4` or any numeric threshold as a blocker.\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 3. EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n45: \n46: - Every `P0` and `P1` finding must include a concrete `file:line` citation.\n47: - Evidence must tie the finding to observed code behavior, not just a general concern.\n48: - `P2` findings should still include specific evidence when available, even if impact is advisory.\n49: - If evidence is incomplete, state the assumption and why the risk still matters.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 4. FINDINGS OUTPUT ORDERING\n54: \n55: - Present findings before summary or praise sections.\n56: - Order findings by severity first: `P0`, then `P1`, then `P2`.\n57: - Keep ordering stable within a severity bucket by impact and confidence.\n58: - Separate required fixes from optional suggestions so merge decisions stay clear.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 5. BASELINE + SURFACE PRECEDENCE\n63: \n64: Apply this skill as the baseline first, then pair it with `sk-code` surface evidence when available:\n65: \n66: - Detected code surface -> `sk-code:<surface>`\n67: - Unclear surfaces -> baseline-only plus explicit uncertainty\n68: \n69: Precedence rules:\n70: \n71: - Baseline security and correctness minimums are always enforced.\n72: - Surface style, process, build, and test conventions override generic baseline guidance.\n73: - Unclear conflicts must be escalated rather than guessed.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 6. BASELINE CHECK FAMILIES\n78: \n79: Mandatory baseline families:\n80: \n81: - Correctness minimums: regression risk, contract safety, spec mismatch, destructive side effects, and boundary handling.\n82: - Security minimums: auth and authorization gaps, injection exposure, unsafe secrets handling, privilege misuse, and reliability risks with security impact.\n83: \n84: These minimums cannot be relaxed by surface guidance.\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 7. FINDING SCHEMA\n89: \n90: Each finding should provide:\n91: \n92: | Field | Requirement |\n93: | --- | --- |\n94: | `id` | Stable label within the review report, such as `P1-001` |\n95: | `severity` | One of `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n96: | `title` | Short, risk-oriented summary |\n97: | `file` | Primary `path:line` location |\n98: | `evidence` | Plain-language explanation tied to observed code |\n99: | `findingClass` | One of `instance-only`, `class-of-bug`, `cross-consumer`, `algorithmic`, `matrix/evidence`, or `test-isolation` |\n100: | `scopeProof` | Grep/test/audit evidence that the recommendation covers same-class sites and consumers, or proves the finding is instance-only |\n101: | `affectedSurfaceHints` | Optional string array of producer/consumer surfaces the fix should address; recommended for actionable findings, required for cross-consumer findings. Use free-form short strings, max about 5 entries. Optional for instance-only findings. |\n102: | `riskScore` | Optional advisory number for relative risk calibration; never gating and never a substitute for `severity` |\n103: | `recommendation` | Specific, scope-proportional fix or follow-up |\n104: \n105: Suggested shape:\n106: \n107: ```markdown\n108: ### P1-001 [P1] Missing authorization check\n109: - File: path/to/file.ts:42\n110: - Evidence: Request handling reaches the write path before role validation.\n111: - Finding class: cross-consumer\n112: - Scope proof: `rg -n \"permission guard|write path\" path/to` shows the write handler is the only unchecked consumer.\n113: - Affected surface hints: [\"request handler\", \"write path\", \"permission guard\"]\n114: - riskScore: 6 (advisory only)\n115: - Recommendation: Enforce the existing permission guard before mutation.\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n121: \n122: - [review_ux_single_pass.md](./review_ux_single_pass.md) - Interactive single-pass report flow and next-step prompts.\n123: - [quick_reference.md](./quick_reference.md) - Lightweight index across baseline review references.\n124: - [security_checklist.md](../assets/security_checklist.md) - Security and reliability checks.\n125: - [code_quality_checklist.md](../assets/code_quality_checklist.md) - Correctness, KISS, DRY, and maintainability checks.\n126: \n127: ---\n\n(End of file - total 127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Review Core Doctrine\ndescription: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"findings first severity ordering\"\n  - \"review finding schema\"\n  - \"severity contract for merge decisions\"\n  - \"evidence file line citation\"\n  - \"baseline surface precedence\"\n  - \"baseline check families\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.5.0.11\n---\n\n# Review Core Doctrine\n\nShared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md","text":"---\ntitle: Review Core Doctrine\ndescription: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"findings first severity ordering\"\n  - \"review finding schema\"\n  - \"severity contract for merge decisions\"\n  - \"evidence file line citation\"\n  - \"baseline surface precedence\"\n  - \"baseline check families\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.5.0.11\n---\n\n# Review Core Doctrine\n\nShared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nShared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SEVERITY DEFINITIONS\n\n| Level | Meaning | Handling |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| P0 | Blocker: exploitable security issue, auth bypass, destructive data loss | Block merge |\n| P1 | Required: correctness bug, spec mismatch, must-fix gate issue | Fix before merge |\n| P2 | Suggestion: non-blocking improvement, documentation polish, style or maintainability follow-up | Optional or schedule follow-up |\n\nEscalation rule: if confidence is low but impact is high, classify toward the higher severity and state the uncertainty explicitly.\n\n### Numeric Severity Calibration\n\nNumeric scores are advisory context, not the gate. A reviewer may add an optional `riskScore` to a finding and adjust it by `+/-2` for local context such as exploitability, blast radius, user impact, confidence, or proven containment. The merge/block decision remains the severity contract above: `P0` blocks, `P1` requires remediation, and `P2` is advisory. Do not adopt `score>=4` or any numeric threshold as a blocker.\n\n---\n\n## 3. EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n- Every `P0` and `P1` finding must include a concrete `file:line` citation.\n- Evidence must tie the finding to observed code behavior, not just a general concern.\n- `P2` findings should still include specific evidence when available, even if impact is advisory.\n- If evidence is incomplete, state the assumption and why the risk still matters.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FINDINGS OUTPUT ORDERING\n\n- Present findings before summary or praise sections.\n- Order findings by severity first: `P0`, then `P1`, then `P2`.\n- Keep ordering stable within a severity bucket by impact and confidence.\n- Separate required fixes from optional suggestions so merge decisions stay clear.\n\n---\n\n## 5. BASELINE + SURFACE PRECEDENCE\n\nApply this skill as the baseline first, then pair it with `sk-code` surface evidence when available:\n\n- Detected code surface -> `sk-code:<surface>`\n- Unclear surfaces -> baseline-only plus explicit uncertainty\n\nPrecedence rules:\n\n- Baseline security and correctness minimums are always enforced.\n- Surface style, process, build, and test conventions override generic baseline guidance.\n- Unclear conflicts must be escalated rather than guessed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. BASELINE CHECK FAMILIES\n\nMandatory baseline families:\n\n- Correctness minimums: regression risk, contract safety, spec mismatch, destructive side effects, and boundary handling.\n- Security minimums: auth and authorization gaps, injection exposure, unsafe secrets handling, privilege misuse, and reliability risks with security impact.\n\nThese minimums cannot be relaxed by surface guidance.\n\n---\n\n## 7. FINDING SCHEMA\n\nEach finding should provide:\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n| --- | --- |\n| `id` | Stable label within the review report, such as `P1-001` |\n| `severity` | One of `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| `title` | Short, risk-oriented summary |\n| `file` | Primary `path:line` location |\n| `evidence` | Plain-language explanation tied to observed code |\n| `findingClass` | One of `instance-only`, `class-of-bug`, `cross-consumer`, `algorithmic`, `matrix/evidence`, or `test-isolation` |\n| `scopeProof` | Grep/test/audit evidence that the recommendation covers same-class sites and consumers, or proves the finding is instance-only |\n| `affectedSurfaceHints` | Optional string array of producer/consumer surfaces the fix should address; recommended for actionable findings, required for cross-consumer findings. Use free-form short strings, max about 5 entries. Optional for instance-only findings. |\n| `riskScore` | Optional advisory number for relative risk calibration; never gating and never a substitute for `severity` |\n| `recommendation` | Specific, scope-proportional fix or follow-up |\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```markdown\n### P1-001 [P1] Missing authorization check\n- File: path/to/file.ts:42\n- Evidence: Request handling reaches the write path before role validation.\n- Finding class: cross-consumer\n- Scope proof: `rg -n \"permission guard|write path\" path/to` shows the write handler is the only unchecked consumer.\n- Affected surface hints: [\"request handler\", \"write path\", \"permission guard\"]\n- riskScore: 6 (advisory only)\n- Recommendation: Enforce the existing permission guard before mutation.\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [review_ux_single_pass.md](./review_ux_single_pass.md) - Interactive single-pass report flow and next-step prompts.\n- [quick_reference.md](./quick_reference.md) - Lightweight index across baseline review references.\n- [security_checklist.md](../assets/security_checklist.md) - Security and reliability checks.\n- [code_quality_checklist.md](../assets/code_quality_checklist.md) - Correctness, KISS, DRY, and maintainability checks.\n\n---","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":127,"totalLines":127,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md","time":{"start":1783921274018,"end":1783921274072}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04843a2490066c82016a547a79cb488191b8c724013071bf3e"}},"id":"prt_f59fe6c9f001QQWkzGyOq4Rtx1","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f59fe12ab001kpdOndufCVF3tM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921274079,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Nk2q8o9sqMMrOXVobWn9Jnja","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Deep Review State Reducer                                                ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: \n5: 'use strict';\n6: \n7: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8: // 1. IMPORTS\n9: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10: \n11: const fs = require('node:fs');\n12: const path = require('node:path');\n13: const { emitResourceMap } = require('../../shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs');\n14: const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('../../runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs');\n15: const { filterCompletionBearingRecords } = require('../../shared/progress/progress-record.cjs');\n16: \n17: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: // 2. CONSTANTS\n19: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: \n21: const REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS = ['correctness', 'security', 'traceability', 'maintainability'];\n22: const SEVERITY_KEYS = ['P0', 'P1', 'P2'];\n23: const SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 };\n24: const LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES = new Set(['new', 'resume', 'restart']);\n25: \n26: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n27: // 3. HELPERS\n28: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n29: \n30: function readUtf8(filePath) {\n31:   return fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n32: }\n33: \n34: function writeUtf8(filePath, content) {\n35:   fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n36:   fs.writeFileSync(filePath, content, 'utf8');\n37: }\n38: \n39: function readJson(filePath) {\n40:   return JSON.parse(readUtf8(filePath));\n41: }\n42: \n43: function getResourceMapEmitSetting(config) {\n44:   const nested = config && typeof config === 'object'\n45:     ? (config.resource_map || config.resourceMap || null)\n46:     : null;\n47:   if (nested && typeof nested === 'object' && typeof nested.emit === 'boolean') {\n48:     return nested.emit;\n49:   }\n50:   return true;\n51: }\n52: \n53: function slugify(value) {\n54:   return value\n55:     .toLowerCase()\n56:     .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-')\n57:     .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, '')\n58:     .slice(0, 80) || 'entry';\n59: }\n60: \n61: function normalizeText(value) {\n62:   if (value === null || value === undefined) return '';\n63:   if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n64:     try { return String(value).replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim(); }\n65:     catch { return ''; }\n66:   }\n67:   return value.replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n68: }\n69: \n70: function escapeRegExp(value) {\n71:   return value.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n72: }\n73: \n74: function zeroSeverityMap() {\n75:   return { P0: 0, P1: 0, P2: 0 };\n76: }\n77: \n78: function isFiniteNumber(value) {\n79:   return typeof value === 'number' && Number.isFinite(value);\n80: }\n81: \n82: function normalizeSeverity(value) {\n83:   return SEVERITY_KEYS.includes(value) ? value : null;\n84: }\n85: \n86: function normalizeLineageMode(value) {\n87:   const normalized = normalizeText(value).toLowerCase();\n88:   return LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES.has(normalized) ? normalized : null;\n89: }\n90: \n91: function getNestedField(record, fieldName) {\n92:   if (!record || typeof record !== 'object') {\n93:     return undefined;\n94:   }\n95:   if (record[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n96:     return record[fieldName];\n97:   }\n98:   if (record.details && typeof record.details === 'object' && record.details[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n99:     return record.details[fieldName];\n100:   }\n101:   return undefined;\n102: }\n103: \n104: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n105: // 4. PARSERS\n106: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n107: \n108: /**\n109:  * Parse JSONL content into an array of records, preserving both iteration and\n110:  * event rows. Backward-compatible array return.\n111:  *\n112:  * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n113:  * @returns {Array<Object>} Parsed records (corrupt lines silently dropped — use parseJsonlDetailed for fail-closed behavior)\n114:  */\n115: function parseJsonl(jsonlContent) {\n116:   return parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent).records;\n117: }\n118: \n119: /**\n120:  * Parse JSONL content and report malformed lines (fail-closed pathway).\n121:  *\n122:  * Returns both the parsed records and a corruption warning list. The reducer\n123:  * exit code is non-zero when warnings are present unless `--lenient` is passed.\n124:  *\n125:  * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n126:  * @returns {{records: Array<Object>, corruptionWarnings: Array<{line: number, raw: string, error: string}>}}\n127:  */\n128: function parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent) {\n129:   const records = [];\n130:   const corruptionWarnings = [];\n131:   let lineNumber = 0;\n132: \n133:   for (const rawLine of jsonlContent.split('\\n')) {\n134:     lineNumber += 1;\n135:     const line = rawLine.trim();\n136:     if (!line) {\n137:       continue;\n138:     }\n139: \n140:     try {\n141:       records.push(JSON.parse(line));\n142:     } catch (error) {\n143:       corruptionWarnings.push({\n144:         line: lineNumber,\n145:         raw: rawLine.length > 200 ? `${rawLine.slice(0, 200)}...` : rawLine,\n146:         error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n147:       });\n148:     }\n149:   }\n150: \n151:   return { records, corruptionWarnings };\n152: }\n153: \n154: function loadDeltaPayloads(deltaDir) {\n155:   if (!fs.existsSync(deltaDir)) {\n156:     return [];\n157:   }\n158: \n159:   return fs.readdirSync(deltaDir)\n160:     .filter((fileName) => /^iter-\\d+\\.jsonl$/.test(fileName))\n161:     .sort((left, right) => left.localeCompare(right, undefined, { numeric: true }))\n162:     .map((fileName) => {\n163:       const { records, corruptionWarnings } = parseJsonlDetailed(readUtf8(path.join(deltaDir, fileName)));\n164:       if (!corruptionWarnings.length) {\n165:         return records;\n166:       }\n167:       console.warn(\n168:         `[deep-review] resource-map extractor skipped ${corruptionWarnings.length} malformed delta row(s) from ${fileName}`,\n169:       );\n170:       return records.concat(new Array(corruptionWarnings.length).fill(null));\n171:     });\n172: }\n173: \n174: function extractSection(markdown, heading) {\n175:   const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)##\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(heading)}\\\\s*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n176:   const match = markdown.match(pattern);\n177:   return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n178: }\n179: \n180: function extractSubsection(sectionText, subheading) {\n181:   const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)###\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(subheading)}[^\\\\n]*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n###\\\\s|\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n182:   const match = sectionText.match(pattern);\n183:   return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n184: }\n185: \n186: function extractListItems(sectionText) {\n187:   return sectionText\n188:     .split('\\n')\n189:     .map((line) => line.trim())\n190:     .filter((line) => /^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/.test(line))\n191:     .map((line) => normalizeText(line.replace(/^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/, '')))\n192:     .filter(Boolean);\n193: }\n194: \n195: /**\n196:  * Parse a finding line of the form: `- **F001**: Title — file:line — Description`\n197:  *\n198:  * @param {string} line - Raw finding bullet\n199:  * @param {string} severity - P0, P1, or P2 context\n200:  * @returns {Object|null} Structured finding or null when the line is not a finding\n201:  */\n202: function parseFindingLine(line, severity) {\n203:   const match = line.match(/^\\*\\*(F\\d+)\\*\\*\\s*:\\s*(.+?)(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+`?([^`]+?)`?)?(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+(.+))?$/);\n204:   if (!match) {\n205:     return null;\n206:   }\n207: \n208:   const [, findingId, title, evidenceRaw, description] = match;\n209:   let file = null;\n210:   let lineNumber = null;\n211: \n212:   if (evidenceRaw) {\n213:     const evidenceMatch = evidenceRaw.trim().match(/^(.+?):(\\d+)(?:[:-].*)?$/);\n214:     if (evidenceMatch) {\n215:       file = evidenceMatch[1];\n216:       lineNumber = Number(evidenceMatch[2]);\n217:     } else {\n218:       file = evidenceRaw.trim();\n219:     }\n220:   }\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 2229. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep Review State Reducer                                                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { emitResourceMap } = require('../../shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs');\nconst { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('../../runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs');\nconst { filterCompletionBearingRecords } = require('../../shared/progress/progress-record.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep Review State Reducer                                                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { emitResourceMap } = require('../../shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs');\nconst { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('../../runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs');\nconst { filterCompletionBearingRecords } = require('../../shared/progress/progress-record.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS = ['correctness', 'security', 'traceability', 'maintainability'];\nconst SEVERITY_KEYS = ['P0', 'P1', 'P2'];\nconst SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 };\nconst LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES = new Set(['new', 'resume', 'restart']);\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction readUtf8(filePath) {\n  return fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n}\n\nfunction writeUtf8(filePath, content) {\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n  fs.writeFileSync(filePath, content, 'utf8');\n}\n\nfunction readJson(filePath) {\n  return JSON.parse(readUtf8(filePath));\n}\n\nfunction getResourceMapEmitSetting(config) {\n  const nested = config && typeof config === 'object'\n    ? (config.resource_map || config.resourceMap || null)\n    : null;\n  if (nested && typeof nested === 'object' && typeof nested.emit === 'boolean') {\n    return nested.emit;\n  }\n  return true;\n}\n\nfunction slugify(value) {\n  return value\n    .toLowerCase()\n    .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-')\n    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, '')\n    .slice(0, 80) || 'entry';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeText(value) {\n  if (value === null || value === undefined) return '';\n  if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n    try { return String(value).replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim(); }\n    catch { return ''; }\n  }\n  return value.replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n}\n\nfunction escapeRegExp(value) {\n  return value.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n}\n\nfunction zeroSeverityMap() {\n  return { P0: 0, P1: 0, P2: 0 };\n}\n\nfunction isFiniteNumber(value) {\n  return typeof value === 'number' && Number.isFinite(value);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSeverity(value) {\n  return SEVERITY_KEYS.includes(value) ? value : null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeLineageMode(value) {\n  const normalized = normalizeText(value).toLowerCase();\n  return LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES.has(normalized) ? normalized : null;\n}\n\nfunction getNestedField(record, fieldName) {\n  if (!record || typeof record !== 'object') {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n  if (record[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n    return record[fieldName];\n  }\n  if (record.details && typeof record.details === 'object' && record.details[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n    return record.details[fieldName];\n  }\n  return undefined;\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. PARSERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Parse JSONL content into an array of records, preserving both iteration and\n * event rows. Backward-compatible array return.\n *\n * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n * @returns {Array<Object>} Parsed records (corrupt lines silently dropped — use parseJsonlDetailed for fail-closed behavior)\n */\nfunction parseJsonl(jsonlContent) {\n  return parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent).records;\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse JSONL content and report malformed lines (fail-closed pathway).\n *\n * Returns both the parsed records and a corruption warning list. The reducer\n * exit code is non-zero when warnings are present unless `--lenient` is passed.\n *\n * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n * @returns {{records: Array<Object>, corruptionWarnings: Array<{line: number, raw: string, error: string}>}}\n */\nfunction parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent) {\n  const records = [];\n  const corruptionWarnings = [];\n  let lineNumber = 0;\n\n  for (const rawLine of jsonlContent.split('\\n')) {\n    lineNumber += 1;\n    const line = rawLine.trim();\n    if (!line) {\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      records.push(JSON.parse(line));\n    } catch (error) {\n      corruptionWarnings.push({\n        line: lineNumber,\n        raw: rawLine.length > 200 ? `${rawLine.slice(0, 200)}...` : rawLine,\n        error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { records, corruptionWarnings };\n}\n\nfunction loadDeltaPayloads(deltaDir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(deltaDir)) {\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  return fs.readdirSync(deltaDir)\n    .filter((fileName) => /^iter-\\d+\\.jsonl$/.test(fileName))\n    .sort((left, right) => left.localeCompare(right, undefined, { numeric: true }))\n    .map((fileName) => {\n      const { records, corruptionWarnings } = parseJsonlDetailed(readUtf8(path.join(deltaDir, fileName)));\n      if (!corruptionWarnings.length) {\n        return records;\n      }\n      console.warn(\n        `[deep-review] resource-map extractor skipped ${corruptionWarnings.length} malformed delta row(s) from ${fileName}`,\n      );\n      return records.concat(new Array(corruptionWarnings.length).fill(null));\n    });\n}\n\nfunction extractSection(markdown, heading) {\n  const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)##\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(heading)}\\\\s*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n  const match = markdown.match(pattern);\n  return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n}\n\nfunction extractSubsection(sectionText, subheading) {\n  const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)###\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(subheading)}[^\\\\n]*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n###\\\\s|\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n  const match = sectionText.match(pattern);\n  return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n}\n\nfunction extractListItems(sectionText) {\n  return sectionText\n    .split('\\n')\n    .map((line) => line.trim())\n    .filter((line) => /^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/.test(line))\n    .map((line) => normalizeText(line.replace(/^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/, '')))\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse a finding line of the form: `- **F001**: Title — file:line — Description`\n *\n * @param {string} line - Raw finding bullet\n * @param {string} severity - P0, P1, or P2 context\n * @returns {Object|null} Structured finding or null when the line is not a finding\n */\nfunction parseFindingLine(line, severity) {\n  const match = line.match(/^\\*\\*(F\\d+)\\*\\*\\s*:\\s*(.+?)(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+`?([^`]+?)`?)?(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+(.+))?$/);\n  if (!match) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const [, findingId, title, evidenceRaw, description] = match;\n  let file = null;\n  let lineNumber = null;\n\n  if (evidenceRaw) {\n    const evidenceMatch = evidenceRaw.trim().match(/^(.+?):(\\d+)(?:[:-].*)?$/);\n    if (evidenceMatch) {\n      file = evidenceMatch[1];\n      lineNumber = Number(evidenceMatch[2]);\n    } else {\n      file = evidenceRaw.trim();\n    }\n  }","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":2229,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","time":{"start":1783921274022,"end":1783921274077}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04843a2490066c82016a547a79cb5081918fff9842e39fdf31"}},"id":"prt_f59fe6ca3001BzxTlfA11tlNpV","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f59fe12ab001kpdOndufCVF3tM"}}
