{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921310242,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gOR94kQvZJO49v42JqEDDSf5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Skill Reference File Templates\n3: description: Comprehensive templates for creating effective reference files for AI agent skills with workflows, decision logic, and validation checkpoints.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"skill reference templates\"\n6:   - \"reference file structure\"\n7:   - \"explicit reasoning references\"\n8:   - \"reference creation guidelines\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: general\n11: version: 1.8.0.16\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Skill Reference File Templates - AI Agent Skills\n15: \n16: Templates for creating reference files in AI agent skills with deep-dive technical guidance.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Location & Naming\n23: \n24: **Location:** `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/references/`\n25: \n26: **Naming Convention:** snake_case with `.md` extension only\n27: \n28: | ✅ Valid Names | ❌ Invalid Names |\n29: |---------------|-----------------|\n30: | `implementation_workflows.md` | `ImplementationWorkflows.md` (PascalCase) |\n31: | `tool_catalog.md` | `tool-catalog.md` (kebab-case) |\n32: | `debugging_guide.md` | `DebuggingGuide.MD` (wrong case) |\n33: | `quick_reference.md` | `quickReference.md` (camelCase) |\n34: | `code_quality_standards.md` | `code quality standards.md` (spaces) |\n35: \n36: ### When to Create References\n37: \n38: **Create a reference file when:**\n39: - Multi-phase workflows with validation checkpoints\n40: - Decision trees with multiple branches\n41: - Pattern libraries with 5+ variations\n42: - Systematic debugging procedures\n43: - Tool integration details\n44: - Content exceeds 200 lines\n45: \n46: **Keep in SKILL.md when:**\n47: - Content under 200 lines\n48: - Simple workflows (3-5 steps)\n49: - Overview and \"When to Use\" sections\n50: - Essential rules (ALWAYS/NEVER/ESCALATE IF)\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 2. DOCUMENT STRUCTURE\n55: \n56: ### Document Structure: Title and Intro\n57: \n58: **CRITICAL: The intro after the H1 title must be 1-2 SHORT sentences only.**\n59: \n60: ```markdown\n61: ---\n62: title: [Title]\n63: description: [One-line description - same as intro]\n64: trigger_phrases:\n65:   - \"[distinctive phrase one]\"\n66:   - \"[distinctive phrase two]\"\n67:   - \"[distinctive phrase three]\"\n68: importance_tier: normal\n69: contextType: general\n70: version: 1.0.0.0\n71: ---\n72: \n73: # [Title]\n74: \n75: [1-2 SHORT sentences only. Brief hook/summary. NO subsections, NO headers here.]\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: \\## 1. OVERVIEW\n80: [All detailed content goes here, NOT in the intro]\n81: \n82: ```\n83: \n84: Every reference file carries this full 5-field frontmatter block: the Skill Advisor harvests it as routing signal (3-8 lowercase multi-word `trigger_phrases` drawn from the doc's content; `importance_tier` defaults to `normal`, `important` only for formal contract docs; `contextType` one of `planning|research|implementation|general`). See [frontmatter_templates.md](../../../shared/assets/frontmatter_templates.md) for field rules.\n85: \n86: > **WARNING: DO NOT duplicate content between intro and Section 1.**\n87: > The intro is a hook; Section 1 provides the details.\n88: \n89: #### GOOD Intro Structure\n90: \n91: ```markdown\n92: # Git Commit Workflows\n93: \n94: Step-by-step workflows for creating clean, atomic commits with proper filtering.\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: \\## 1. OVERVIEW\n99: \n100: ### Purpose\n101: Provides systematic workflows for analyzing changes, filtering artifacts, and creating well-structured commits.\n102: \n103: ### When to Use\n104: - Creating commits with multiple file changes\n105: - Filtering generated files from commits\n106: - Writing clear commit messages\n107: \n108: ### Core Principle\n109: Atomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.\n110: ```\n111: \n112: #### BAD Intro Structure (duplicates content)\n113: \n114: ```markdown\n115: # Git Commit Workflows\n116: \n117: Step-by-step workflows for creating clean, atomic commits with proper filtering.\n118: \n119: ### Core Principle   ← WRONG: No headers in intro!\n120: Atomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.\n\n(Showing lines 1-120 of 1025. Use offset=121 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Skill Reference File Templates\ndescription: Comprehensive templates for creating effective reference files for AI agent skills with workflows, decision logic, and validation checkpoints.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"skill reference templates\"\n  - \"reference file structure\"\n  - \"explicit reasoning references\"\n  - \"reference creation guidelines\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.8.0.16\n---\n\n# Skill Reference File Templates - AI Agent Skills\n\nTemplates for creating reference files in AI agent skills with deep-dive technical guidance.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md","text":"---\ntitle: Skill Reference File Templates\ndescription: Comprehensive templates for creating effective reference files for AI agent skills with workflows, decision logic, and validation checkpoints.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"skill reference templates\"\n  - \"reference file structure\"\n  - \"explicit reasoning references\"\n  - \"reference creation guidelines\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.8.0.16\n---\n\n# Skill Reference File Templates - AI Agent Skills\n\nTemplates for creating reference files in AI agent skills with deep-dive technical guidance.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Location & Naming\n\n**Location:** `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/references/`\n\n**Naming Convention:** snake_case with `.md` extension only\n\n| ✅ Valid Names | ❌ Invalid Names |\n|---------------|-----------------|\n| `implementation_workflows.md` | `ImplementationWorkflows.md` (PascalCase) |\n| `tool_catalog.md` | `tool-catalog.md` (kebab-case) |\n| `debugging_guide.md` | `DebuggingGuide.MD` (wrong case) |\n| `quick_reference.md` | `quickReference.md` (camelCase) |\n| `code_quality_standards.md` | `code quality standards.md` (spaces) |\n\n### When to Create References\n\n**Create a reference file when:**\n- Multi-phase workflows with validation checkpoints\n- Decision trees with multiple branches\n- Pattern libraries with 5+ variations\n- Systematic debugging procedures\n- Tool integration details\n- Content exceeds 200 lines\n\n**Keep in SKILL.md when:**\n- Content under 200 lines\n- Simple workflows (3-5 steps)\n- Overview and \"When to Use\" sections\n- Essential rules (ALWAYS/NEVER/ESCALATE IF)\n\n---\n\n## 2. DOCUMENT STRUCTURE\n\n### Document Structure: Title and Intro\n\n**CRITICAL: The intro after the H1 title must be 1-2 SHORT sentences only.**\n\n```markdown\n---\ntitle: [Title]\ndescription: [One-line description - same as intro]\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"[distinctive phrase one]\"\n  - \"[distinctive phrase two]\"\n  - \"[distinctive phrase three]\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# [Title]\n\n[1-2 SHORT sentences only. Brief hook/summary. NO subsections, NO headers here.]\n\n---\n\n\\## 1. OVERVIEW\n[All detailed content goes here, NOT in the intro]\n\n```\n\nEvery reference file carries this full 5-field frontmatter block: the Skill Advisor harvests it as routing signal (3-8 lowercase multi-word `trigger_phrases` drawn from the doc's content; `importance_tier` defaults to `normal`, `important` only for formal contract docs; `contextType` one of `planning|research|implementation|general`). See [frontmatter_templates.md](../../../shared/assets/frontmatter_templates.md) for field rules.\n\n> **WARNING: DO NOT duplicate content between intro and Section 1.**\n> The intro is a hook; Section 1 provides the details.\n\n#### GOOD Intro Structure\n\n```markdown\n# Git Commit Workflows\n\nStep-by-step workflows for creating clean, atomic commits with proper filtering.\n\n---\n\n\\## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nProvides systematic workflows for analyzing changes, filtering artifacts, and creating well-structured commits.\n\n### When to Use\n- Creating commits with multiple file changes\n- Filtering generated files from commits\n- Writing clear commit messages\n\n### Core Principle\nAtomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.\n```\n\n#### BAD Intro Structure (duplicates content)\n\n```markdown\n# Git Commit Workflows\n\nStep-by-step workflows for creating clean, atomic commits with proper filtering.\n\n### Core Principle   ← WRONG: No headers in intro!\nAtomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":120,"totalLines":1025,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md","time":{"start":1783921310225,"end":1783921310241}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03b49908c9a32738016a547a9e0e808191a3ab3d18250d2155"}},"id":"prt_f59fefa06001A7lZUNx7akOodY","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f59fec928001cz11FYpcd93kU5"}}
