{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921582469,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kR8AgJLmssagNVOZrmCnLanx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","offset":240,"limit":28},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n240: ```javascript\n241: // ✅ GOOD: Never store sensitive data in localStorage\n242: sessionStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');  // Non-sensitive data OK\n243: \n244: // ❌ BAD: Store sensitive data\n245: localStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\n246: localStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **Cookies:**\n250: ```javascript\n251: // ✅ GOOD: Secure, HttpOnly cookies (server-side)\n252: Set-Cookie: session=abc123; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict\n253: \n254: // ❌ BAD: JavaScript-accessible cookies with sensitive data\n255: document.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Accessible to XSS\n256: ```\n257: \n258: **Checklist:**\n259: - [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage/sessionStorage\n260: - [ ] Cookies set with Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite attributes\n261: - [ ] Sensitive data encrypted if stored client-side\n262: - [ ] Clear storage on logout\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n\n(End of file - total 265 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Never store sensitive data in localStorage\nsessionStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');  // Non-sensitive data OK\n\n// ❌ BAD: Store sensitive data\nlocalStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\nlocalStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n```\n\n**Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Secure, HttpOnly cookies (server-side)\nSet-Cookie: session=abc123; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict\n\n// ❌ BAD: JavaScript-accessible cookies with sensitive data\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Accessible to XSS\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage/sessionStorage","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","text":"```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Never store sensitive data in localStorage\nsessionStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');  // Non-sensitive data OK\n\n// ❌ BAD: Store sensitive data\nlocalStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\nlocalStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n```\n\n**Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Secure, HttpOnly cookies (server-side)\nSet-Cookie: session=abc123; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict\n\n// ❌ BAD: JavaScript-accessible cookies with sensitive data\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Accessible to XSS\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage/sessionStorage\n- [ ] Cookies set with Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite attributes\n- [ ] Sensitive data encrypted if stored client-side\n- [ ] Clear storage on logout\n\n---\n","lineStart":240,"lineEnd":265,"totalLines":265,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","time":{"start":1783921582447,"end":1783921582465}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02a1958afd928bbf016a547bae540c81918c28d5a47d4489a8"}},"id":"prt_f5a03216d001scOawpjS39UZFr","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f5a02b626001lylFAY3uxE1sCP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921582469,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lpFEFzZoY5RNW2ci81YXbqxn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md","offset":20,"limit":44},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Cross-library best practices for third-party integrations, plus a summary of the supported libraries and what each one is for.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Choosing among the supported third-party libraries\n29: - Applying cross-library integration best practices (CDN loading, version pinning, error handling)\n30: - Looking up what a given library is for\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. BEST PRACTICES\n35: \n36: ### CDN Loading Pattern\n37: \n38: ```javascript\n39: // ✅ Good: Version pinned, origin-allowlisted, async, error handled\n40: const CDN_URL = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/library@{version}';\n41: const ALLOWED_CDN_HOSTS = ['cdn.jsdelivr.net', 'unpkg.com'];\n42: \n43: async function load_with_timeout(url, timeout_ms = 10000) {\n44:   // Never inject an unvalidated URL as a script src — restrict to trusted CDN origins.\n45:   let parsed;\n46:   try { parsed = new URL(url); } catch { return false; }\n47:   if (parsed.protocol !== 'https:' || !ALLOWED_CDN_HOSTS.includes(parsed.hostname)) {\n48:     return false;\n49:   }\n50: \n51:   return new Promise((resolve) => {\n52:     const timer = setTimeout(() => resolve(false), timeout_ms);\n53: \n54:     const script = document.createElement('script');\n55:     script.src = parsed.href;\n56:     script.async = true;\n57:     // Add Subresource Integrity when the hash is known: script.integrity = 'sha384-…'; script.crossOrigin = 'anonymous';\n58:     script.onload = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(true); };\n59:     script.onerror = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(false); };\n60:     document.head.appendChild(script);\n61:   });\n62: }\n63: \n\n(Showing lines 20-63 of 183. Use offset=64 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nCross-library best practices for third-party integrations, plus a summary of the supported libraries and what each one is for.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Choosing among the supported third-party libraries\n- Applying cross-library integration best practices (CDN loading, version pinning, error handling)\n- Looking up what a given library is for\n\n---\n\n## 2. BEST PRACTICES\n\n### CDN Loading Pattern\n\n```javascript\n// ✅ Good: Version pinned, origin-allowlisted, async, error handled","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md","text":"## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nCross-library best practices for third-party integrations, plus a summary of the supported libraries and what each one is for.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Choosing among the supported third-party libraries\n- Applying cross-library integration best practices (CDN loading, version pinning, error handling)\n- Looking up what a given library is for\n\n---\n\n## 2. BEST PRACTICES\n\n### CDN Loading Pattern\n\n```javascript\n// ✅ Good: Version pinned, origin-allowlisted, async, error handled\nconst CDN_URL = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/library@{version}';\nconst ALLOWED_CDN_HOSTS = ['cdn.jsdelivr.net', 'unpkg.com'];\n\nasync function load_with_timeout(url, timeout_ms = 10000) {\n  // Never inject an unvalidated URL as a script src — restrict to trusted CDN origins.\n  let parsed;\n  try { parsed = new URL(url); } catch { return false; }\n  if (parsed.protocol !== 'https:' || !ALLOWED_CDN_HOSTS.includes(parsed.hostname)) {\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => resolve(false), timeout_ms);\n\n    const script = document.createElement('script');\n    script.src = parsed.href;\n    script.async = true;\n    // Add Subresource Integrity when the hash is known: script.integrity = 'sha384-…'; script.crossOrigin = 'anonymous';\n    script.onload = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(true); };\n    script.onerror = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(false); };\n    document.head.appendChild(script);\n  });\n}\n","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":63,"totalLines":183,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md","time":{"start":1783921582449,"end":1783921582467}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02a1958afd928bbf016a547bae54148191b04e929d8584348a"}},"id":"prt_f5a032170001uZBOC0MAcJMBad","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f5a02b626001lylFAY3uxE1sCP"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921582469,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gTf5hEiPiDWccdefGQ2nmhgU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","offset":80,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n80: ```\n81: \n82: **Checklist:**\n83: - [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n84: - [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n85: - [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n86: - [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n87: - [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n88: \n89: ### CSRF Protection\n90: \n91: **SameSite Cookies:**\n92: ```javascript\n93: // ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite on a non-sensitive, client-set cookie (e.g. a UI preference)\n94: document.cookie = \"ui_theme=dark; SameSite=Strict; Secure; Path=/\";\n95: \n96: // ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\n97: document.cookie = \"ui_theme=dark\";  // Sent on cross-site requests\n98: ```\n99: \n100: > Session tokens must NOT be set via `document.cookie` — a JavaScript-set cookie cannot be `HttpOnly`, so it is readable by XSS. Session cookies belong in a server-set `Set-Cookie: … Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict` header (see the Sensitive Data Storage section). Use client-set cookies only for non-sensitive values.\n101: \n102: **CSRF Tokens:**\n103: ```html\n104: <!-- ✅ GOOD: Include CSRF token in forms -->\n105: <form method=\"POST\">\n106:   <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"csrf_token\" value=\"${csrfToken}\">\n107:   <input type=\"text\" name=\"username\">\n108:   <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n109: </form>\n\n(Showing lines 80-109 of 265. Use offset=110 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n- [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n- [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n- [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n- [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n\n### CSRF Protection\n\n**SameSite Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite on a non-sensitive, client-set cookie (e.g. a UI preference)\ndocument.cookie = \"ui_theme=dark; SameSite=Strict; Secure; Path=/\";\n\n// ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"ui_theme=dark\";  // Sent on cross-site requests\n```\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","text":"```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n- [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n- [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n- [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n- [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n\n### CSRF Protection\n\n**SameSite Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite on a non-sensitive, client-set cookie (e.g. a UI preference)\ndocument.cookie = \"ui_theme=dark; SameSite=Strict; Secure; Path=/\";\n\n// ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"ui_theme=dark\";  // Sent on cross-site requests\n```\n\n> Session tokens must NOT be set via `document.cookie` — a JavaScript-set cookie cannot be `HttpOnly`, so it is readable by XSS. Session cookies belong in a server-set `Set-Cookie: … Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict` header (see the Sensitive Data Storage section). Use client-set cookies only for non-sensitive values.\n\n**CSRF Tokens:**\n```html\n<!-- ✅ GOOD: Include CSRF token in forms -->\n<form method=\"POST\">\n  <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"csrf_token\" value=\"${csrfToken}\">\n  <input type=\"text\" name=\"username\">\n  <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n</form>","lineStart":80,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":265,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","time":{"start":1783921582444,"end":1783921582468}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02a1958afd928bbf016a547bae54088191885a17613ff09b6e"}},"id":"prt_f5a03216a001u7YJXjBPVBaI75","sessionID":"ses_0a6050609ffeLmwfdMHnBWCS8d","messageID":"msg_f5a02b626001lylFAY3uxE1sCP"}}
