ated structural sites are clean; F001 remains as bounded intro-length polish. |\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n - **P0:** 0 active\n - **P1:** 0 active\n-- **P2:** 0 active\n-- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n+- **P2:** 1 active\n+- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +1 P2\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Current-state full-corpus validation and direct reads distinguish fixed defects from stale historical reports.\n+- Iteration 1: forced validator replay plus independent semantic checks closed the four prior defect classes without relying on the generic validator alone.\n \n ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n \n - `memory_match_triggers` timed out twice; canonical packet documents and repository evidence are the context source.\n \n ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n \n-- None at initialization.\n+- Full-corpus metadata/filename/wrapper/numbering/link regression scan -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration 1); do not repeat unless a later finding changes current-state evidence.\n \n ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n - Completed pivots: 0\n - Failed pivots: 0\n - Audited overrides: 0\n-- Swept: none\n+- Swept: correctness structure matrix\n - Pivot lineage: none\n-- Remaining frontier: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability\n+- Remaining frontier: security, traceability, maintainability\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n-- None at initialization.\n+- Recurrence of the four xHigh-remediated structural defects: ruled out by direct current reads and the complete corpus matrix (iteration 1).\n+- Broad frontmatter, filename, numbering, Related Resources, or renamed-link regression: ruled out across 163 paths (iteration 1).\n \n ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n-- Dimension: correctness\n-- Focus: full 163-file mechanical/semantic matrix and direct replay of the four xHigh-remediated structural sites.\n+- Dimension: security\n+- Focus: documentation-only delivery boundary plus current replay of the two security examples remediated by sibling packet 020.\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n \n@@ -90,9 +92,9 @@\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n \n | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n |---|---|---|---:|---|\n-| `spec_code` | core | pending | 0 | Current-state replay pending |\n+| `spec_code` | core | partial | 1 | Core structure passes; F001 is a bounded P2 intro-length mismatch. |\n | `checklist_evidence` | core | pending | 0 | Strict packet validation replay pending |\n | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | notApplicable | 0 | No feature catalog in target scope |\n | `playbook_capability` | overlay | notApplicable | 0 | No executable playbook capability claimed |\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n@@ -101,13 +103,13 @@\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n \n | File or root | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n |---|---|---:|---|---|\n-| Packet docs and generated metadata | none | 0 | 0 | pending |\n-| Create-skill templates and validator | none | 0 | 0 | pending |\n-| code-opencode references/assets | none | 0 | 0 | pending |\n-| code-webflow references/assets | none | 0 | 0 | pending |\n-| code-quality assets | none | 0 | 0 | pending |\n+| Packet docs and generated metadata | D1 | 1 | 0 | partial |\n+| Create-skill templates and validator | D1 | 1 | 0 | partial |\n+| code-opencode references/assets | D1 | 1 | 1 P2 | partial |\n+| code-webflow references/assets | D1 | 1 | 1 P2 shared class | partial |\n+| code-quality assets | D1 | 1 | 0 | partial |\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n","additions":18,"deletions":16}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-b/prompts/iteration-1.m