4 @@\n \n | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n |---|---|---:|---|\n | D1 Correctness | PASS with advisory | 1 | Four remediated structural sites are clean; F001 remains as bounded intro-length polish. |\n+| D2 Security | PASS | 2 | Documentation-only delivery confirmed; sibling 020 security remediations close both prior hypotheses. |\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n - **P0:** 0 active\n - **P1:** 0 active\n - **P2:** 1 active\n-- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +1 P2\n+- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Current-state full-corpus validation and direct reads distinguish fixed defects from stale historical reports.\n - Iteration 1: forced validator replay plus independent semantic checks closed the four prior defect classes without relying on the generic validator alone.\n+- Iteration 2: current file reads plus scoped history separated packet 019's structural delivery from sibling 020's content-security closure.\n \n ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n \n - `memory_match_triggers` timed out twice; canonical packet documents and repository evidence are the context source.\n@@ -60,22 +62,23 @@\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n - Completed pivots: 0\n - Failed pivots: 0\n - Audited overrides: 0\n-- Swept: correctness structure matrix\n+- Swept: correctness structure matrix; security delivery boundary and prior content findings\n - Pivot lineage: none\n-- Remaining frontier: security, traceability, maintainability\n+- Remaining frontier: traceability, maintainability\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n - Recurrence of the four xHigh-remediated structural defects: ruled out by direct current reads and the complete corpus matrix (iteration 1).\n - Broad frontmatter, filename, numbering, Related Resources, or renamed-link regression: ruled out across 163 paths (iteration 1).\n+- Executable, credential, authorization, unsafe cookie, and unvalidated script-source regressions: ruled out by current evidence (iteration 2).\n \n ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n-- Dimension: security\n-- Focus: documentation-only delivery boundary plus current replay of the two security examples remediated by sibling packet 020.\n+- Dimension: traceability\n+- Focus: run both hard protocols, replay strict packet validation, and reconcile completion claims with current evidence.\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n \n@@ -103,12 +106,12 @@\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n \n | File or root | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n |---|---|---:|---|---|\n-| Packet docs and generated metadata | D1 | 1 | 0 | partial |\n+| Packet docs and generated metadata | D1, D2 | 2 | 0 | partial |\n | Create-skill templates and validator | D1 | 1 | 0 | partial |\n-| code-opencode references/assets | D1 | 1 | 1 P2 | partial |\n-| code-webflow references/assets | D1 | 1 | 1 P2 shared class | partial |\n+| code-opencode references/assets | D1, D2 | 2 | 1 P2 | partial |\n+| code-webflow references/assets | D1, D2 | 2 | 1 P2 shared class | partial |\n | code-quality assets | D1 | 1 | 0 | partial |\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n","additions":12,"deletions":9}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-b/prompts/iteration-2.md\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-b/iterations/iteration-002.md\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-b/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-b/deep-review-state.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-b/