ION FRONTIER\n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n67: - Completed pivots: 0\n68: - Failed pivots: 0\n69: - Audited overrides: 0\n70: - Swept: correctness structure matrix; security delivery boundary; both traceability protocols\n71: - Pivot lineage: none\n72: - Remaining frontier: maintainability and stabilization replay\n73: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n74: \n75: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n76: \n77: - Recurrence of the four xHigh-remediated structural defects: ruled out by direct current reads and the complete corpus matrix (iteration 1).\n78: - Broad frontmatter, filename, numbering, Related Resources, or renamed-link regression: ruled out across 163 paths (iteration 1).\n79: - Executable, credential, authorization, unsafe cookie, and unvalidated script-source regressions: ruled out by current evidence (iteration 2).\n80: - A deliverable regression as the cause of strict failure: ruled out; F002 is an evidence-packaging gate failure (iteration 3).\n81: \n82: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n83: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n84: - Dimension: maintainability and stabilization\n85: - Focus: replay F001-F003, inspect same-class residuals, and verify registry stability before synthesis.\n86: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n87: \n88: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n89: \n90: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n91: \n92: - Target pointers: five canonical packet docs; description/graph metadata; 163 tracked Markdown paths under code-opencode references/assets, code-webflow references/assets, and code-quality assets.\n93: - Behavior claims: required metadata and four-part version; snake_case basenames; H1/intro/Overview ordering; mode-specific Overview content; contiguous numbering; terminal Related Resources; renamed-file link integrity.\n94: - Authority: `skill_reference_template.md`, `skill_asset_template.md`, and `validate_document.py`.\n95: - Current-state evidence before iteration 1: generic validation is 163/163; no hyphenated basename; no missing metadata/version; no Overview-order, numbering, R